From Suresh Thennarangam Research Scholar Subject Re Mix GL with X Xlib Xt mwm pyeatt Larry Pyeatt writes In article Jay Graham writes XmDrawingArea for drawing with But I would like to take advantage of the Graphics Library GL available on our IBM RS SGI's GL i believe Is it possible to mix X and GL in one application program Can I use GL subroutines in an XmDrawingArea or in an X window opened by me with XOpenWindow You can't make GL calls in an XmDrawingArea widget for There is a widget already defined for It is the GlxMDraw motif or GlxDraw athena It is similar to a XmDrawingArea except that it allows you to use GL calls to render into the Look at glxlink glxunlink glxgetconfig and glxwinset in the man The GlxMDraw widget works pretty OpenGL will be an I can vouch for The GL Widget works pretty I have been using it for sometime I'm not sure though whether you can use Xlib calls to draw into the GL I haven't tried it yet nor have I read the accompanying documentation Try posting to for more Better still you will find most of the answers in the SGI manuals there is a little transition guide which explains the mixed model programming paradigm Mixing X and GL Does PEX graPHIGS have the same functionality of GL I think GL is a little easier to use and a little more powerful but that's just an Mileage may Well PEX is designed as an extension to X and will be more seamless but then it is buggy to start with opinions o o o Suresh Thennarangam EMail Internet Research Scholar ISSST Institute Of Systems Science Tel National University Of Singapore Heng Mui Keng Terrace Telex ISSNUS RS Singapore